{
  "text": "An important part of projected SL trends on a regional scale arises from the dynamical and thermal and haline adjustment of the ocean related to changes in the circulation. On timescales up to decades, model improvements are needed to better capture the interannual variability of SL associated with climate modes discussed in section \"Causes of Coastal Sea Level Variability\" (e.g., [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . Simulations of such variability by climate models require further validation with emerging longer data sets of SL, mass or density changes.",
  "correct_citation": {
